As flagship smartphones continue to improve in quality, their price tags also become larger. There are clear benefits that flagship smartphones offer over cheaper alternatives, but many people cannot justify spending more than R20,000 on a smartphone. Many smartphone users may simply need a reliable device that offers decent performance and a good camera. For these users, there are a number of smartphones available for under R5,000 that fit the bill. We have listed some of the best smartphones available in South Africa that fit these criteria. Pricing for these smartphones is sourced from Takealot. The Xiaomi Redmi Note 8 was, until recently, the latest entrant in the Chinese smartphone maker’s Note range. It sports a quad-lens camera system, which is impressive in its price range. <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-358489" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/xiaomi-redmi-note-8-640x427.jpg" alt="xiaomi redmi note 8" width="640" height="427" srcset="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/xiaomi-redmi-note-8-640x427.jpg 640w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/xiaomi-redmi-note-8-600x400.jpg 600w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/xiaomi-redmi-note-8-768x512.jpg 768w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/xiaomi-redmi-note-8-1200x800.jpg 1200w, https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/xiaomi-redmi-note-8.jpg 1323w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> The Samsung Galaxy A30s is the option that targets the R5,000 price range from Samsung’s extensive list of smartphones. Sporting solid specifications across the board, this is a great option for those looking for a mid-range smartphone from the reliable Samsung brand. The Huawei Y7 2019 is a great option for users who want a reliable smartphone while saving some money compared to other smartphones closer to the R5,000 price point. It serves as a great mid-point in the range of smartphones available around the R2,000 and R5,000 price points. The Xiaomi Redmi Note 9S is an impressive upgrade from Xiaomi’s Note 8 range. It sports an improved quad-lens camera system and a large battery. The Huawei Y7p is Huawei’s latest entry into the sub-R4,000 market. It offers users a triple-lens camera system and impressive specifications across the board for a smartphone in this price range. The Hisense Infinity H40 Rock is a solid competitor from a brand other than Huawei, Samsung, and Xiaomi. It offers an HD+ display and an impressive 5,510mAh battery, while this version also comes with ‘Battery Armour’ – which offers an additional 4,500mAh battery power. The Huawei Y9 Prime offers great value, including a triple-lens camera system, 4GB ram, and 128GB storage. It also has a 16MP pop-up selfie camera, which is a useful feature and stands out at this price range. The Samsung Galaxy A21s is another great option from Samsung. It includes a quad-lens camera system and supports Bluetooth 5.0. The Nokia 5.3 is a great alternative to the Samsung, Huawei, and Xiaomi options already discussed. It offers a quad-lens camera, 64GB of storage, and an octa-core processor.